bird reserve island Langenwerder. For 2011 1,568 birds(+/- 5 \%.) were
detected on the image mosaic, based on multispectral image
classification and {GIS}-based post processing. Based on the experiences
of 2011 the results and the accuracy of the automatic bird count 2012
became more efficient. For 2012 1,938 birds with an accuracy of approx.
+/- 3 \% were counted. Additionally a separation of breeding and
non-breeding birds was performed with the assumption, that standing
birds cause a visible shade. The final section of the paper is devoted
to the analysis of the 3D-point cloud. Thereby the point cloud was used
to determine the height of the vegetation and the extend and depth of
closed sinks, which are unsuitable for breeding birds.},
