ntified habitat thresholds corresponding to open canopy structure, moderate densities of large and medium pines, and sparse hardwood midstory trees. Selection ranks prioritized multiple thresholds below {USFWS} range-wide recovery thresholds, indicating site-specific management goals may be beneficial for {RCW} conservation. Fine-grained {LiDAR}-derived habitat data coupled with {GPS}-derived habitat use can guide forest bird conservation by identifying the full range of structural conditions associated with threshold responses.},
