ories in ecology is, to some degree, illusory. As was mentioned above, several "theories" (see table S1) are actually specific hypotheses or models. Ecologists and other scientists often use the terms model and theory indistinguishably (e.g., Leijonhufvud 1997, Ginzburg and Jensen 2004), but they are fundamentally different. Models are {BioScience} 64: 701-710.},
