ows {ALS} data to be seamlessly integrated into existing conventional stand-level, operational, tactical, or strategic forest inventories, thereby enabling within-polygon variability to be characterized, while at the same time not precluding the implementation of standard or mandated inventory practices. Additional background material and a full listing of rec-ommendations for best practices are provided in the guide. While the guide focuses on the generation of forest inventory attributes from {ALS} data, there are many additional benefits offered by the {ALS} data. For example, the generation of a high-quality digital elevation model from the {ALS} data enables improved planning for road and block layout, slope stability and risk assessment, improved riparian mapping,},
